    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "Do I need to install anything before using this skill?",
        "answer": "Yes. You need to install the RunComfy CLI using npm i -g @runcomfy/cli and authenticate with runcomfy login or by setting the RUNCOMFY_TOKEN environment variable."
      },
      {
        "question": "Which AI models does this skill support?",
        "answer": "This skill routes to 11+ models including FLUX 2 variants, Google Nano Banana 2 and Pro, OpenAI GPT Image 2, ByteDance Seedream 5 and 4-5, Dreamina 4-0, Alibaba Qwen Image, Z-Image Turbo, and Wan 2-7."
      },
      {
        "question": "How does the skill choose which model to use?",
        "answer": "The skill analyzes your request and selects the optimal model based on your intent - typography precision uses GPT Image 2, photorealism uses Seedream 5, speed iteration uses Nano Banana 2 or FLUX 2 Klein 4B."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I edit images that I already have?",
        "answer": "Yes. Use image-to-image routes like Nano Banana 2 Edit or GPT Image 2 Edit by providing image URLs. The skill preserves the main subject while applying your requested changes."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is there support for open-weights and custom models?",
        "answer": "Yes. Models like Qwen Image, Wan 2-7, and Z-Image Turbo support open-weights workflows and LoRA-compatible endpoints for custom model integration."
      },
      {
        "question": "How are API tokens handled securely?",
        "answer": "The runcomfy login command stores your token in ~/.config/runcomfy/token.json with restricted permissions (mode 0600). For CI environments, use the RUNCOMFY_TOKEN environment variable instead."
      }
